<a href="http://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E7%83%B7%E7%83%83">zh:烷烃</a></p>	
<h1>Android (robot)</h1>

<p>An <b>android</b> is a <a href="" title="robot">robot</a>&#60;ref name=&#34;Van Riper 10&#34;&#62; &#60;/ref&#62; or <a href="" title="synthetic biology">synthetic organism</a>&#60;ref name=&#34;Dinello109&#34;&#62; &#60;/ref&#62; designed to look and act like a human. Although &#34;android&#34; is used almost universally to refer to both sexes, and those of no particular sex, &#34;Android&#34; technically refers to the male form, while &#34;<a href="" title="Gynoid">Gynoid</a>&#34; is  the feminine form. Until recently, androids have largely remained within the domain of <a href="" title="science fiction">science fiction</a>, frequently seen in film and television.</p>
